00:39.800 --> 00:41.560
The world
will have to deal with us.

00:42.880 --> 00:44.680
<i>Previously on The 4400...</i>

00:44.800 --> 00:46.120
<i>You're
the alternative we need</i>

00:46.320 --> 00:48.760
<i>to Collier and his
promicin-pushing radicals.</i>

00:49.160 --> 00:50.840
Does that mean you'll run
for city council?

00:50.920 --> 00:52.560
It means I'm gonna run
and I'm gonna win.

00:52.640 --> 00:55.200
I intend on attacking you
right up until the day of the election.

00:55.480 --> 00:58.600
There are a lot of people out there
that are afraid of what you represent.

00:58.800 --> 01:02.120
<i>I have my eye on something greater
than just city council.</i>

01:02.760 --> 01:04.680
<i>- You hate all the 4400.
- So what if I do?</i>

01:04.800 --> 01:07.320
<i>I have reason to believe
that you're capable of terrible things,</i>

01:07.440 --> 01:10.320
and that you have an evil
living inside of you.

01:10.440 --> 01:12.520
I'm supposed to eliminate
the 4400.

01:12.600 --> 01:16.080
All this talk of a catastrophe
the 4400 are supposed to prevent?

01:16.160 --> 01:18.200
- It's lies.
- So you keep telling me.

01:20.560 --> 01:22.400
<i>Everything in that book
is going to come true.</i>

01:22.520 --> 01:24.360
Collier will lead
the human race to salvation.

01:24.520 --> 01:25.560
You will help him.

01:30.280 --> 01:31.760
<I>I found the guy for the job.

01:34.640 --> 01:36.200
<i>His name's Robert Shaftoe.</i>

01:38.920 --> 01:40.120
<i>Ex-Marine.</i>

01:41.200 --> 01:42.240
<i>Dead-eye sniper.</i>

01:43.120 --> 01:44.480
<i>He did some work
for our...</i>

01:44.640 --> 01:46.960
<i>organization,
out of Kansas City.</i>

01:48.600 --> 01:50.160
<i>If you want someone killed,</i>

01:50.600 --> 01:52.400
<i>until they're completely dead,</i>

01:53.000 --> 01:54.440
<i>then Shaftoe's your man.</i>

01:57.240 --> 01:58.200
<i>Sounds good.</i>

01:58.680 --> 01:59.640
<i>Bring him in.</i>

01:59.720 --> 02:01.480
<i>Are you sure
you wanna go through with this?</i>

02:01.960 --> 02:04.280
<i>Because once I bring Shaftoe
through that door,</i>

02:04.600 --> 02:05.800
<i>there's no going back.</i>

02:06.200 --> 02:07.160
<i>The target...</i>

02:07.520 --> 02:08.479
<i>is a dead man.</i>

02:09.639 --> 02:11.320
<i>- Completely.
- Oh, my God.</i>

02:11.440 --> 02:14.000
Come on, the acting, the dialogue,
this is horrendous.

02:14.080 --> 02:16.040
- Marco, why are we watching this?
- Just, shh...

02:16.120 --> 02:17.520
The best part's coming up.

02:29.640 --> 02:31.120
<i>The assignment is dangerous.</i>

02:31.280 --> 02:33.440
<i>In fact, it might be
the most dangerous assignment</i>

02:33.560 --> 02:35.000
<i>you've ever been assigned.</i>

02:35.360 --> 02:36.480
<i>But if you succeed,</i>

02:37.120 --> 02:38.600
<i>the danger will be worth it.</i>

02:39.320 --> 02:40.320
<i>And the rewards?</i>

02:41.640 --> 02:43.680
<i>They will be worth...
the danger.</i>

02:46.320 --> 02:48.080
<i>Danger is my business.</i>

02:49.240 --> 02:50.720
<i>Consider the target dead.</i>

02:55.120 --> 02:56.160
<i>Completely...</i>

02:56.880 --> 02:57.840
<i>dead.</i>

02:58.280 --> 03:00.200
That's our guy.
That's Curtis Peck.

03:01.360 --> 03:03.000
He's an original recipe 4400.

03:03.240 --> 03:04.200
Correction...

03:04.320 --> 03:07.320
- He's our favorite original recipe.
- Before he disappeared,

03:07.480 --> 03:09.600
Curtis wrote, directed,
and starred in horror movies.

03:10.080 --> 03:11.480
Real low-Budget stuff.

03:11.560 --> 03:13.320
You know,
the sets were mostly in his house.

03:13.400 --> 03:14.400
The actors?

03:14.520 --> 03:16.200
Pretty much
just his friends and family.

03:16.320 --> 03:18.000
Really?
I never would have guessed.

03:18.160 --> 03:19.400
After he came back,

03:19.520 --> 03:20.720
Curtis kept on making movies,

03:20.880 --> 03:21.880
but he shifted genres.

03:22.240 --> 03:24.280
Each one of his movies
is about an unsolved mystery.

03:25.160 --> 03:27.400
He did one about
Jimmy Hoffa's disappearance.

03:27.520 --> 03:29.160
He filmed a costume drama
in his backyard

03:29.280 --> 03:31.040
about the lost colonies at Roanoke.

03:31.160 --> 03:33.120
You just saw his take
on JFK's assassination.

03:33.280 --> 03:35.480
That's great, Marco.
I'm glad this guy has a hobby.

03:35.640 --> 03:37.120
It's not just a hobby.

03:37.240 --> 03:39.640
Some people think that
making these films

03:39.800 --> 03:42.360
- is Curtis's 4400 ability.
- Come on, guys,

03:42.440 --> 03:44.400
you're not telling us
that that movie...

03:44.520 --> 03:46.720
tells us what really happened
to president Kennedy?

03:46.840 --> 03:48.120
There's no way
to know for sure,

03:48.240 --> 03:49.960
but, I mean,
there really is an ex-Marine

03:50.080 --> 03:51.280
named Robert Shaftoe,

03:51.400 --> 03:54.640
and he really was in Dallas
on november 22nd, 1963.

03:54.760 --> 03:56.600
You can't prove Curtis is right,

03:56.720 --> 03:58.280
but you also can't deny

03:58.360 --> 04:00.320
that his theories are compelling.

04:00.400 --> 04:02.120
Some people want to think
everything is a conspiracy,

04:02.240 --> 04:04.040
and I'm sure that this guy
is really appealing to them,

04:04.120 --> 04:05.680
but, Marco,
we've got  a lot of stuff on our plate,

04:05.760 --> 04:07.720
and we just don't have time
to look into something

04:07.800 --> 04:09.600
that might be a 4400 ability.

04:09.840 --> 04:11.800
Don't think I could sit through
another one of those movies.

04:12.520 --> 04:14.760
We didn't ask you down here
to tell you about his ability.

04:15.320 --> 04:16.279
Curtis disappeared.

04:16.560 --> 04:17.519
Nobody can find him.

04:18.320 --> 04:21.079
About 10 days ago,
he stopped posting on his myspace page.

04:21.200 --> 04:23.280
We noticed, so we tried
to get in touch with him.

04:24.160 --> 04:26.800
He's not picking up the phone,
he's not answering emails.

04:27.040 --> 04:29.000
I know, I know,
no big deal, right?

04:29.320 --> 04:32.760
I wasn't really worried
until he missed his last NTAC check-in.

04:33.800 --> 04:35.600
Curtis Peck has dropped off the map.

04:35.760 --> 04:37.280
Somebody should look into it.

04:46.680 --> 04:48.160
- What is this place?
- I don't know,

04:48.240 --> 04:50.080
Cassie just said
we should come here.

04:53.200 --> 04:54.760
I think it's an old bomb shelter.

04:56.960 --> 04:59.880
We should be safe here. It doesn't look
like anyone's been here in years.

05:00.320 --> 05:02.080
I don't understand
why we came to Seattle.

05:02.240 --> 05:04.360
We just led a hundred people
into a city

05:04.440 --> 05:06.120
where everyone's looking for us.

05:06.600 --> 05:09.120
Nobody has a place to stay.
Nobody knows what to do next.

05:09.280 --> 05:11.360
Are you telling me
this is the answer?

05:12.600 --> 05:14.880
- This place is a mess.
- We'll repair it.

05:16.240 --> 05:18.040
Thank you for finding this for us.

05:18.760 --> 05:20.840
You have a truly
extraordinary ability.

05:22.880 --> 05:24.160
Get everyone settled in.

05:25.200 --> 05:26.280
This place is perfect.

05:26.640 --> 05:27.640
We begin here.

05:34.240 --> 05:36.240
How much you wanna bet
we're about to wake up a man

05:36.320 --> 05:37.680
with a crushing  hangover?

05:44.240 --> 05:45.160
Curtis!

05:45.560 --> 05:46.720
Curtis Peck!

05:56.080 --> 05:57.640
You think someone
broke into the place?

05:57.760 --> 05:59.800
Maybe, or else this guy's
as bad at housekeeping

05:59.880 --> 06:01.280
as he is at making movies.

06:03.360 --> 06:06.600
It doesn't look like anything's missing.
All his video equipment is sitting here.

06:08.000 --> 06:09.720
Are you looking for Curtis?

06:10.160 --> 06:11.880
Yes, we are.
We're from NTAC.

06:12.000 --> 06:13.720
- Do you know him?
- Of course.

06:13.880 --> 06:14.960
I'm Neal Handler.

06:15.920 --> 06:17.840
I live around back.
I'm Curtis' neighbor.

06:18.880 --> 06:20.880
And... his collaborator.

06:21.400 --> 06:23.440
I'm proud to say
I've been in more of his movies

06:23.600 --> 06:24.720
than anyone else.

06:25.040 --> 06:27.520
- Yeah, we've... seen your work.
- Thank you.

06:29.560 --> 06:32.400
I haven't seen Curtis in a few days.
Is he all right?

06:32.640 --> 06:34.880
Well, that's what
we're trying to find out.

06:35.040 --> 06:37.200
Do you know
if Curtis had any enemies,

06:37.320 --> 06:39.360
or anyone who might want
to break into his house?

06:39.480 --> 06:40.640
Enemies?

06:41.040 --> 06:42.000
Take your pick.

06:42.240 --> 06:44.400
The CIA, the mafia...

06:44.560 --> 06:45.840
the freemasons.

06:46.000 --> 06:48.000
Curtis exposed
a lot of people.

06:48.360 --> 06:49.320
So you...

06:49.680 --> 06:51.200
you believe his movies are real?

06:51.840 --> 06:53.080
Of course.

06:53.760 --> 06:55.880
That's why
they brought him back

06:56.000 --> 06:57.840
in a ball of light.

06:58.320 --> 07:01.720
To tell the truth
to a reluctant world!

07:05.040 --> 07:06.080
I'll tell you what, though,

07:07.080 --> 07:08.720
if someone did toss this place,

07:09.200 --> 07:12.000
I can guarantee you they didn't find
what they were looking for.

07:12.840 --> 07:13.800
Curtis has...

07:14.280 --> 07:15.560
a secret hiding place.

07:16.120 --> 07:17.760
He keeps his journal in there.

07:17.920 --> 07:19.240
All his script notes.

07:19.400 --> 07:20.680
Could you show it to us?

07:21.440 --> 07:23.440
We just want to help out your friend,
That's all.

07:23.560 --> 07:25.320
We really like his movies, too.

07:25.480 --> 07:27.320
I mean,
we just saw the one on JFK,

07:27.440 --> 07:30.160
and it was... good.
You were really good.

07:31.240 --> 07:32.200
It's here.

07:36.000 --> 07:36.960
Here.

07:37.120 --> 07:39.440
Curtis uses those
for inspiration.

07:47.800 --> 07:50.920
<i>If you're watching this,
then that means I'm in trouble.</i>

07:51.400 --> 07:52.760
<i>Deep trouble.</i>

07:53.040 --> 07:55.920
<i>Don't believe anything you hear
about a car accident or a suicide.</i>

07:56.040 --> 07:58.240
<i>If I'm gone,
it's because they came after me.</i>

08:00.160 --> 08:02.560
<i>I have an idea for a new movie.</i>

08:02.680 --> 08:04.360
<i>It's big.
It's so big,</i>

08:04.440 --> 08:06.600
<i>it's going to change everything
if I get to make it,</i>

08:06.720 --> 08:08.320
<i>and that's
what they're scared of.</i>

08:13.880 --> 08:15.720
<i>That's them.
They're here now.</i>

08:15.920 --> 08:17.960
<i>You need to know,
Jordan Collier...</i>

08:18.080 --> 08:20.320
<i>the 4400... they're not the ones
you should be scared of.</i>

08:20.440 --> 08:22.600
<i>There's something else out there,
something worse,...</i>

08:22.680 --> 08:25.240
<I>it's much worse,
and they're coming for me now.

